bTI7800_NOTIFICATIONS_MIB.contactinfo: Technical Support BTI Systems Inc. 200-1000 Innovation Drive Kanata, Ontario, Canada, K2K 3E7 NA Toll Free: +1 866-431-4967 International: +1 613-239-4781 support@btisystems.com
bTI7800_NOTIFICATIONS_MIB.description: The bti7800-conditions submodule defines the data modeling that supports the retrieval of active alarms and conditions on the BTI7800 system.

entityName.name: entityName
entityName.description: The entityName identifies the system-unique name of the entity against which the condition is raised.

code.name: code
code.description: Identifies the type of condition raised.

reportType.name: reportType
reportType.description: If set to non-alarmed, the list entry is a non-alarmed condition. If set to alarmed, the entry is an alarmed condition.

timeStamp.name: timeStamp
timeStamp.description: The date and time at which the condition became active.

severity.name: severity
severity.description: The severity level of the condition.

serviceAffecting.name: serviceAffecting
serviceAffecting.description: If true, the condition is known to disrupt the normal service provided by the entity.

description.name: description
description.description: Provides a description of the condition raised that may include context specific information.
